      "author": "sergiogportela",
      "description": "## Fix: accented characters in @path references\n\n@path links now resolve correctly when filenames contain accented characters (á, é, ç, ã, ô, etc.), which is common in Portuguese and other languages.\n\n### What changed\n- Path-matching regexes now use Unicode property escapes (`\\p{L}`, `\\p{M}`) instead of ASCII-only `\\w`\n- Fixes both Live Preview and Reading mode\n- Also handles decomposed Unicode forms (macOS HFS+ filenames)",
      "draft": false,
      "name": "1.1.1",
      "prerelease": false,
      "publishedAt": "2026-02-23T17:44:34Z",
      "tag": "1.1.1"
